# skill: security-review
# purpose: Code security review (Security Persona - Phase 2)
# triggers: Code ready for security review

## Invocation
```
security-review <task-id> [--code-dir <code-directory>] [--threat-model <threat-model-file>]
```

## Output
Creates: `memory/tasks/<task-id>/security-review.md`

## Implementation Flow

### 1. Load Context
```bash
#!/bin/bash
# security-review.skill implementation

TASK_ID="$1"
CODE_DIR="${2:-.}"
THREAT_MODEL="${3:-memory/tasks/$TASK_ID/threat-model.md}"

TASK=$(cat "memory/tasks/$TASK_ID/input.json")

if [ -f "$THREAT_MODEL" ]; then
    TM_CONTENT=$(cat "$THREAT_MODEL")
fi
```

### 2. Security Scans
```bash
# Run static analysis
run_security_scans() {
    local code_dir="$1"

    echo "Running security scans..."

    # SAST - Static Application Security Testing
    if command -v semgrep &> /dev/null; then
        echo "Running Semgrep..."
        semgrep scan "$code_dir" --config auto --json > "memory/tasks/$TASK_ID/semgrep-results.json"
    fi

    # Dependency scanning
    if command -v pip-audit &> /dev/null; then
        echo "Checking Python dependencies..."
        pip-audit "$code_dir" > "memory/tasks/$TASK_ID/pip-audit-results.txt" 2>&1
    fi

    if command -v npm audit &> /dev/null; then
        echo "Checking Node.js dependencies..."
        npm audit --json > "memory/tasks/$TASK_ID/npm-audit-results.json" 2>&1
    fi

    # Secret scanning
    if command -v gitleaks &> /dev/null; then
        echo "Scanning for secrets..."
        gitleaks detect --source "$code_dir" --report-path "memory/tasks/$TASK_ID/gitleaks-results.json"
    fi
}
```

### 3. Code Review Checklist
```markdown
# Security Review: <task-id>

## Review Info
**Task:** $TASK_ID
**Reviewed:** $(date +%Y-%m-%d)
**Reviewer:** <agent-name>

## Automated Scan Results

### SAST Results
$(if [ -f "memory/tasks/$TASK_ID/semgrep-results.json" ]; then
    echo "```"
    cat "memory/tasks/$TASK_ID/semgrep-results.json" | jq '.results | length'
    echo "findings"
    echo "```"
else
    echo "SAST not run or no results"
fi)

### Dependency Vulnerabilities
$(if [ -f "memory/tasks/$TASK_ID/npm-audit-results.json" ]; then
    echo "Advisories: $(cat memory/tasks/$TASK_ID/npm-audit-results.json | jq '.metadata.vulnerabilities')"
fi)

### Secrets Detected
$(if [ -f "memory/tasks/$TASK_ID/gitleaks-results.json" ]; then
    echo "Secrets found: $(cat memory/tasks/$TASK_ID/gitleaks-results.json | jq '.violations | length')"
fi)

## Manual Code Review

### Authentication
| Check | Status | Notes |
|-------|--------|---|
| Passwords hashed with strong algorithm | ✓/✗ | <notes> |
| Session tokens are secure | ✓/✗ | <notes> |
| Multi-factor authentication | ✓/✗ | <notes> |
| Token expiration configured | ✓/✗ | <notes> |

### Authorization
| Check | Status | Notes |
|-------|--------|---|
| RBAC implemented | ✓/✗ | <notes> |
| Authorization checks on all endpoints | ✓/✗ | <notes> |
| No hardcoded roles/permissions | ✓/✗ | <notes> |

